    "Moreover, selecting an appropriate embedding model is crucial (Ganguli et al., 2024).",
    "By contrast, unsupervised methods require no pre-labeled examples.",
    "Instead, they infer categories from the data itself, using NLP-derived features ranging from simple keywords (Yoon and Park, 2004; Hu, Li, Yao, Yu, Yang and Hu, 2018; Bergeaud, Potiron and Raimbault, 2017) to multi-dimensional embeddings.",
    "A prominent example is the Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) topic model introduced by Blei, Ng and Jordan (2003), often likened to principal component analysis (PCA) for text.",
    "Here, documents are first transformed via a vectorization technique-such as TF-IDF-and LDA identifies patterns of co-occurring terms, grouping them into so-called \"topics.\""
